Functions
+++++++++

The functions with name ``MyFunc1``, ``MyFunc2``, input types ``T1``, ``T2``, ``T3`` and output type ``T``, are declared by:

.. code::

    myFunc1, myFunc2 : T1 ‚®Ø T2 ‚®Ø T3 ‚Üí T

Their name should not start with a capital letter, by convention.
The ASCII equivalent of ``‚®Ø`` is ``*``, and of ``‚Üí`` is ``->``.

IDP-Z3 does not support partial functions.


The following introspection functions are built-ins:

* ``arity: Symbol ‚Üí Symbol`` yields the arity of a symbol;
* ``input_domain : Symbol ‚®Ø ‚Ñ§ ‚Üí Symbol`` yields the n-th input-domain of a symbol;
* ``output_domain: Symbol ‚Üí Symbol`` yields the output domain of a symbol.

